fields.Title: WHIRLING F1 / LOGIC WHITE CHECK
fields.Description: The logic white check where you present your theory of how Ruby killed Lely and get the Hardie boys to give up her approximate location.

fields.Title: Logic: "Here you go: access to the roof, we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Here you go: access to the roof, weapon, and motive. That's not too hard. And here is what you can do to make it even easier -- c'mon guys!

fields.Title: You: ""Just making an observation. Let's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just making an observation. Let's move on."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes." (Roll your eyes.) "Female in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." (Roll your eyes.) "Female intuition. That's what it was. You're right Eugene."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay..." The lieutenant steps in...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay..." The lieutenant steps in. "We've ruled out infighting. That's how this works: by exclusion. Remember, all we need to do is rule Ruby out too. That's all this is."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Alright -- she took a fucking leak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright -- she took a fucking leak, okay? For one moment. *Maybe* went out too -- she has an operation to run from her lorry." He points to the intersection. "We're not getting into what that *operation* is again, cop."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No, you can't. I know what you did..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, you can't. I know what you did here on the weekend. People talk -- and what they say doesn't sound like a science-cop. You're a madman."

fields.Title: You: ""There's a 72% chance that the bull..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a 72% chance that the bullet came from the roof."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Wouldn't hurt to have one of those..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wouldn't hurt to have one of those in Martinaise." He nods. "Still -- all the labs in the world don't put her on that roof. How did she get there? Climb?"

fields.Title: You: ""I know. It's bewildering for me to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know. It's bewildering for me too, but that's what she said."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""All right, cop." He nods. "Keep ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right, cop." He nods. "Keep talking. I'll tell you when I've had enough."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""*Maybe* from the coast? I've been..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Maybe* from the coast? I've been too busy with this shit to see if it's possible. So no." He shakes his head. "I don't think it was a sniper. It was close up."
fields.Alternate1: "*Maybe* from the coast? But like I said, I've been too busy dealing with you idiots. So no." He shakes his head. "I don't think it was a sniper. It was close up."
fields.Alternate2: "*Maybe* from the coast? But like I said, I've been too busy dealing with you, copper. So no." He shakes his head. "I don't think it was a sniper. It was close up."

fields.Title: You: ""Recent." (Nod.) "Size about 43.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Recent." (Nod.) "Size about 43."

fields.Title: You: ""She could have just been covering..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She could have just been covering up for *herself*, Titus."

fields.Title: You: ""Ruby could have gotten to the roof..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby could have gotten to the roof from somewhere *inside* the Whirling."

fields.Title: Glen: ""She didn't either! She would never..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She didn't either! She would never do that." The blond man looks around. "Why aren't more of you defending her? This is fucking stupid, Titus."

fields.Title: Logic: "Ooh! So he didn't rule her out comp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ooh! So he didn't rule her out completely? *And* she's skipped town. This is good.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""It's just two doors. We're not giv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's just two doors. We're not giving you *Ruby* for that -- she's one of *us*."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There's *another*, right on the ro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's *another*, right on the roof, next to Klaasje's window. How about that? You been through that door?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Well, god damn..." His eyes follow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, god damn..." His eyes follow the evidence bag back in your pocket. "It's not proof, but it's a possible murder weapon -- close to her. Too damn close."

fields.Title: Theo: "The old man in the corner nods."
fields.Dialogue Text: The old man in the corner nods.

fields.Title: You: ""Me, personally?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Me, personally?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You know, when I first saw you lim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know, when I first saw you limp in here I thought she was paranoid, or sniffing her own supply, but..." He measures you up. "Now I'm not so sure."

fields.Title: Alain: "Silence. He nods."
fields.Dialogue Text: Silence. He nods.

fields.Title: You: "Shake it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shake it.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Right. That's the second one now wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Right. That's the second one now who's trying to flee you.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah, there was something else. Sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, there was something else. She wouldn't tell me though. I could see she wanted to. It was *burning* on her lips: 'This cop, Titus, this cop, he...' But she was too scared."

fields.Title: Logic: "Sure. It was someone else. It appea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sure. It was someone else. It appears we have a *ninth* Hardie boy.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Where have you looked for her, mor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where have you looked for her, more precisely?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Just me, huh? Wow. Well... Good luc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just me, huh? Wow. Well... Good luck!

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I see. But what's back there, I me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I see. But what's back there, I mean -- storage rooms or shit?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""While we cannot say for certain ri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "While we cannot say for certain right *now*, we *will* find out."

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""We were talkin' about radio equipm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We were talkin' about radio equipment. She said she's doing Ulan frequencies and a pale-something. I don't know more."

fields.Title: You: "Give up."
fields.Dialogue Text: Give up.

fields.Title: Logic: "Shush. I'm just more level headed t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shush. I'm just more level headed than you. That's my thing. Let's look at this as a learning experience. What are the components you need to implicate Ruby?

fields.Title: Logic: "Smart move. The components are: acc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smart move. The components are: access to the roof, weapon, and motive. Here is what you can do to make it easier -- c'mon guys!

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "For starters, you could find out wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For starters, you could find out what's behind that mystery door in the kitchen. If it's a secret route, she could have used that to get to the roof!

fields.Title: Glen: ""She *organizes* things. She doesn'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She *organizes* things. She doesn't whack people. That's not the kind of person she is. She's a... talker."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "He gestures with his beer can -- so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He gestures with his beer can -- so you haven't won him over yet! That bad boy goes down on the table only when he's completely focused on something else.

fields.Title: Glen: ""Boss, but maybe..." The blond guy..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boss, but maybe..." The blond guy interjects. "A single machine like that is worth over 500 reál."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant opens his notes. "Su..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant opens his notes. "Sunday night 11:30 to 12:15 -- she was here *all* that time?"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Behind his squinting eyes, dominoes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Behind his squinting eyes, dominoes are falling -- fast. It's all beginning to make sense to him now.

fields.Title: You: ""She is part of the *homo-sexual un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She is part of the *homo-sexual underground*."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "You're going to have to be way more..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're going to have to be way more blunt here.

fields.Title: You: "Better not push it, back to other i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Better not push it, back to other ideas.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Yeah -- no. Ruby's got more balls..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- no. Ruby's got more balls than a ball pit. You'd have to be an idiot not to..." He looks around. "Guys, I'm not the only one who knew, right?"

fields.Title: Logic: "You don't need to *prove* anything...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't need to *prove* anything. Doubt is enough for now -- and Titus *must* have some.

fields.Title: Shanky: ""If she used us... then that's a se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If she used us... then that's a serious violation of the *Hardie code*, boss."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You're on thin ice here, asshole."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're on thin ice here, asshole." He points at you.

fields.Title: Glen: ""T, we're not seriously considering..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "T, we're not seriously considering it, are we?!" He almost gets up from his seat. "Ruby wouldn't do this. Why would she do something like this?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Think about it -- why go through a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Think about it -- why go through all that effort? It was her idea, wasn't it? The hanging? You went along, but she suggested it."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Fuck you, man, I would never fuck..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck you, man, I would never fuck my guys over like that." He squeaks with indignation.

fields.Title: Alain: ""I don't know, cop -- why don't you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know, cop -- why don't you find your *lost gun* first?" The tattooed man bursts out laughing at his own joke.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""What do you mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean?"

fields.Title: Alain: ""Then why the fuck was he asking yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then why the fuck was he asking you for *your* gun, huh? When he tried shooting himself or some shit... Because he doesn't *have* his own!"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Yeah, the bitch is jacketed alrigh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, the bitch is jacketed alright. 4 mm too..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yes, she *could* have. This is one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, she *could* have. This is one *looooong* shot." He shakes his head, but the look in his eyes shows interest.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Next he's gonna kill himself -- ag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Next he's gonna kill himself -- again." The tattooed man looks at you with disdain.

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""I will boss." The man reaches in h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I will boss." The man reaches in his overalls for a cigarette.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""So she *may* have access to semiau..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So she *may* have access to semiautomatics. But that's a long fucking stretch of the imagination."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""All right, I'll play along. Those..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right, I'll play along. Those two doors of yours -- the winch connects them? With some kind of... dumbwaiter?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""She knew there's evidence on her -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She knew there's evidence on her -- and she knew we'd find it. This is typical suspect behaviour. Why fleeing is always incriminatory."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""I'm sorry. God, why does everythin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry. God, why does everything flee at the sight of my shadow?!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He shrugs. "Lizzie needed some air...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He shrugs. "Lizzie needed some air."

fields.Title: You: ""Do you have any clues on where Rub..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you have any clues on where Ruby went?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""She's not really a..." The man sta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She's not really a..." The man stares into his beer. "Hardie candidate anymore, is she?"

fields.Title: You: "That will only piss him off. He's n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That will only piss him off. He's not going to yap about Evrart.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Why not? You suck on that gun like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why not? You suck on that gun like someone tore you a brand new asshole."

fields.Title: Logic: "Suit yourself! But remember, you're..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Suit yourself! But remember, you're the one putting yourself through this hassle.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I think it's best we just dive in,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it's best we just dive in," he whispers back, before turning to Titus and asking: "What makes you so sure Ruby *didn't* kill him?"

fields.Title: Logic: "... No one?"
fields.Dialogue Text: ... No one?

fields.Title: You: ""Wild stuff, Titus. Stuff you're no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wild stuff, Titus. Stuff you're not prepared to believe."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Boyish. Hair's red, dyed. She look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boyish. Hair's red, dyed. She looks like a lorryman."

fields.Title: Logic: "Could this *complex operation* be t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could this *complex operation* be the one Joyce asked you to look into? Probably, though they'll never open up about it. You'll have to keep investigating!

fields.Title: Logic: "You know this already. It all fits..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know this already. It all fits together: Ruby, the missing Hardie, was present at the hanging and running the drug trade.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Can't get through the door? You kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Can't get through the door? You know what would help -- doing a *thorough* search of this room! Maybe something's hidden.

fields.Title: You: ""Good one, Kim.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good one, Kim."

fields.Title: Drama: "That's a lie."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's a lie.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That close, huh? How fortunate. I'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That close, huh? How fortunate. I'll take a thorough look at those prints myself before I believe that, cop."

fields.Title: You: ""Recent." (Nod.) "A week or two.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Recent." (Nod.) "A week or two."
fields.Alternate1: "They were about a week or two old."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Knew what?" The man can't believe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Knew what?" The man can't believe what he's hearing. "First he says she murdered him -- now she's a *f*g* too? It's a lie!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "Glen here obviously likes men and h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Glen here obviously likes men and he can't hack it. That's his thing and you do *not* want to get into it. Moving on.

fields.Title: You: ""Shanky, let's assume you killed hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shanky, let's assume you killed him..."

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe there's more.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe there's more."

fields.Title: You: ""How much do you guys know about th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How much do you guys know about this place?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Twenty, maybe thirty rifles, Titus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Twenty, maybe thirty rifles, Titus. Also broken -- but still, there were too many. And there must be other caches too."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""I'm on it, boss. Right when the la..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm on it, boss. Right when the law clears, me and Angus are going up there."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It was in *your* box. I take it Ru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was in *your* box. I take it Ruby has been in here?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He doesn't wait for a response. "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't wait for a response. "This goes against your everyone-has-a-gun theory. If it was a military-grade, how'd *Ruby* get it?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm just being up front with what..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just being up front with what I know."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He doesn't wait for a response. "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't wait for a response. "This goes against your short-range theory. If the murder weapon was military-grade, how did *Ruby* get it?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Just a thought experiment. Let's g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just a thought experiment. Let's go on." He nods for you to continue.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I've seen the winch, I'm not blind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've seen the winch, I'm not blind." He nods. "You sayin' she reeled herself up by her collar. Like some kind of..." he can't come up with an analogy.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I told you -- you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I told you -- you."

fields.Title: Volition: "Wow, you've been very thorough. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow, you've been very thorough. There's nothing else to add -- just crack that Klaasje's defences. Maybe she'll tell you something helpful?

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure, cop, sure..." he turns the E..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, cop, sure..." he turns the Eugene. "We need to have a look at that secret passage, boys."

Physical Instrument: "Get a move on, asshole! Stop standi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Get a move on, asshole! Stop standing with your dick in your hand.

fields.Dialogue Text: Stop drooling. Run around or something. Hit yourself in the face. *Anything*. No one has any idea what to do with you if you just stand here.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Yeah, some people have their shit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, some people have their shit together. What's wrong with that?"
fields.Alternate1: "Yeah, some people have their shit together -- unlike you. What's wrong with that?"

fields.Title: Alain: ""Nah, man. That's just Ruby. She's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, man. That's just Ruby. She's got shit under control," the man explains. "That's her whole thing. That's why she's so good."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Well, let old Titus set your mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, let old Titus set your mind at ease then -- she didn't do it. She was here all night."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A more serious consideration -- th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A more serious consideration -- that you wish to avoid -- is that she knew what happened, because she did it."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Okay, but..." The man looks around..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but..." The man looks around. "How'd she get up? There's no room for a staircase in this building. *Or* an elevator, for that matter."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Fuck you..." The man can't believe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck you..." The man can't believe what he's hearing. "First he says she murdered him -- now she's a *f*g* too? It's a lie!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And just 'cause she was gone for f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And just 'cause she was gone for five minutes doesn't mean she *magically* got to the roof and shot him." He taps on his temple. "I've been through this -- it's not plausible."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No-no," he squints at you. "Let's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no," he squints at you. "Let's get *into* it -- what did she say?"

fields.Title: You: "No time to waste on this."
fields.Dialogue Text: No time to waste on this.

fields.Title: You: ""Sex. She wanted sex from her.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sex. She wanted sex from her."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""The *what* now?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The *what* now?"

fields.Title: You: ""Would you prefer to go on trial wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Would you prefer to go on trial with your men  -- as part of a lynch mob -- or alone, for cold blooded murder?"

fields.Title: You: ""An *exceptional* sniper could have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "An *exceptional* sniper could have done it."

fields.Title: You: "Wait -- that would go against the t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait -- that would go against the theory I'm presenting here.

fields.Title: You: ""There's a locked door in the kitch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a locked door in the kitchen -- and another on the roof. Ever been through those?"

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Wow, man, can we? I mean...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow, man, can we? I mean..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Just making sure we're on the same..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just making sure we're on the same page." The lieutenant pretends to take a note. "It doesn't all fit. We're just sharing info -- candidly."

fields.Title: Logic: "It doesn't *all* have to fit. The c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It doesn't *all* have to fit. The chance is still way smaller than it coming from the roof. And he knows it.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""So it had to come from a breech-lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So it had to come from a breech-loading rifle. Military-grade." He turns to you. "Not even you militia-monkeys have those."

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Boss..." The big guy in the corner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boss..." The big guy in the corner speaks up with a wheeze. "There's this strange blue door in the kitchen. I've been there..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""On the side of the building. You c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "On the side of the building. You can see it from the harbour." He points to his eyeballs. "You wanna be a lieutenant -- you gotta keep your eyes peeled."

fields.Title: Alain: ""What winch? Where's the winch?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What winch? Where's the winch?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Let's go with that. Point is -- it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's go with that. Point is -- it's just a rusty winch, it doesn't put her on the roof."

fields.Title: You: ""Why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Asshole till the end, huh. Well, f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Asshole till the end, huh. Well, fuck you too, then!" He doesn't sound angry, despite shouting.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""A little -- on the coast.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A little -- on the coast."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""When are you gonna get it through..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When are you gonna get it through your dumb head?" He scoffs. "I already *am*, I just wasn't sure you were."
fields.Alternate1: "When are you gonna get it through your suicidal head?" he scoffs. "I already *am* -- I just wasn't sure you were."

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know what she's doing with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know what she's doing with Ulan frequencies?"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Stop thinking about your lost gun,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop thinking about your lost gun, dammit. You'll get a heart attack.

fields.Title: Logic: "There we go. Your mind is a relaxed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There we go. Your mind is a relaxed muscle. It's so nice and easy to give up, isn't it? On the downside -- you have no idea what you were supposed to do now. I could have *debriefed* you.

fields.Title: Volition: "You're not an idiot. Don't say that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're not an idiot. Don't say that. This is a really big mess and being a detective is hard.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He's *thinking*. Let the man think..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's *thinking*. Let the man think." The lieutenant defends you.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I don't know what to say to that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know what to say to that."

fields.Title: Drama: "Say: "Five hundred Lears and I can'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say: "Five hundred Lears and I can't remember the first line!!!"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Fucking hell..." The blond man is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fucking hell..." The blond man is in some kind of anguish that makes him stare into his garlic bread bowl, intently.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Wishful thinking has no place in a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wishful thinking has no place in a police investigation," the lieutenant tells Alain, his voice mild but firm.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Hmhm. People say there was a pinba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmhm. People say there was a pinball arcade here, some time before the hostel -- what was it called, Theo?"

fields.Title: Authority: "There's a bit of truth in there for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a bit of truth in there for Titus to react so brashly. He does not like his authority questioned.

fields.Title: You: ""Really, nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Really, nothing."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Just 'cause she was gone for five..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just 'cause she was gone for five minutes doesn't mean she *magically* got to the roof and shot the merc." He taps on his temple. "I've been through this -- it's not plausible."

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing. They where just there.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing. They where just there."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I don't like guessing, cop. *No on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't like guessing, cop. *No one* does."

fields.Title: You: ""Have you noticed the winch out bac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have you noticed the winch out back? On the outer wall of the Whirling?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Titus, you're not *really* saying...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Titus, you're not *really* saying..."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "So this is why Shanky doesn't like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So this is why Shanky doesn't like her. Useful for you -- it makes him advocate against Ruby.

fields.Title: You: ""She did tell us right before we ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She did tell us right before we arrested her."

fields.Title: You: ""There were pinball machines in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There were pinball machines in the workshop. Still operational."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Goddamn it, cop -- are you kidding..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Goddamn it, cop -- are you kidding me? You know it was no goddamn Pinball Murderer!"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Just don't contradict yourself. If..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just don't contradict yourself. If it doesn't sound like 'RUBY DID IT', maybe keep it to yourself?

fields.Title: Alain: ""I don't. All I see is a cop who's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't. All I see is a cop who's about to kill himself -- again."

fields.Title: You: ""Have we firmly established Ruby co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have we firmly established Ruby could have had access to the roof where the man was shot?" (Move on.)

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "But what if you miss interesting in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But what if you miss interesting information that way? The choice is ultimately yours, but...

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""She was afraid I would tell you."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She was afraid I would tell you." He looks  you straight in the eye. "Maybe she was right. By now I probably would."

fields.Title: You: ""Can you tell me where on the coast..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you tell me where on the coast I should start looking?"

fields.Title: You: ""You should be a cop, Titus.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You should be a cop, Titus."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Rich-boy law is a sham." He shakes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Rich-boy law is a sham." He shakes his hand. "It only works for the Wild Pines lady. So keep your lab -- and watch your ass out there."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "*Who's* doing this looking? They're..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Who's* doing this looking? They're all here.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And I suppose you have a theory on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And I suppose you have a theory on that?"

fields.Title: You: "Walla-walla-bing-bang?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Walla-walla-bing-bang?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Thank you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, she's just got her *shit toge..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, she's just got her *shit together*. That's how she knew."

fields.Title: Theo: ""East Delta Pinball Arcade." The ol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "East Delta Pinball Arcade." The old man coughs. "*Weird* place -- went bankrupt."

fields.Title: You: ""From there -- a door leads straigh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "From there -- a door leads straight to the roof. You can just step outside."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "That's probably for the best. Don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's probably for the best. Don't break your stride now.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""This is *some* sordid shit." The b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is *some* sordid shit." The big man rubs his chin. "It's also the kind of garbage our Miss Oranje puts out to cover her own ass."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And that's okay. Some are queerer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And that's okay. Some are queerer than others, you can still be a Hardie." He glances at Glen. "But if you bring your own personal shit into our outfit..."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Yeah and they don't put her on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah and they don't put her on the roof either. It's just mambo jumbo. He hasn't got shit."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Girls like girls too, Angus," the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Girls like girls too, Angus," the lieutenant explains. "Sometimes. This is one of those times -- she liked Klaasje."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I know what you've been thinking,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know what you've been thinking, Glen. We'll talk about it -- once the murder charges have been cleared."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's a thought exercise, Titus," h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a thought exercise, Titus," he explains. "Think. You kill him. Get up there. Shoot him. Get down..."

fields.Title: You: ""It was her idea, right? The hangin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was her idea, right? The hanging?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Easy now, Glen." He turns to you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Easy now, Glen." He turns to you. "What he's is trying to say is -- people who don't have guns don't shoot people. You need a gun for that. And you can't prove she has one."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "On this mere cameo. I get it. Movin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On this mere cameo. I get it. Moving on.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That looks antique -- a Belle-Magr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That looks antique -- a Belle-Magrave..." He takes the gun, inspects it and hands it back to you. "It's inoperable. Where'd you get it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Goes against your little theory, d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Goes against your little theory, doesn't it?" He rubs his chin. "Then again I've known few people in my life who own more than one pair of boots -- and occasionally do change them..."

fields.Title: Composure: "He looks tough but there is a nervo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks tough but there is a nervous twitch in his dark green eye. This is all too close to home for him.

fields.Title: You: ""The local pawnshop sold my lost gu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The local pawnshop sold my lost gun to a woman. Maybe it was her?"

fields.Title: Alain: ""We just missed one. Ruby doesn't k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We just missed one. Ruby doesn't know this place boss -- just these cops, diggin' up shit."

fields.Title: You: ""What if the doors are *connected?*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if the doors are *connected?* She could've gone up -- shot him -- come down -- in well under five minutes."
fields.Alternate1: "*Connected* -- with the *winch*, Eugene! She could've gone up -- shot him -- come down -- in well under five minutes."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""He's been fuckin' *eating* in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's been fuckin' *eating* in the kitchen!" The rat-faced man explodes. "The cop and the lardo don't have shit."

fields.Title: Authority: "Titus doesn't reply -- probably a g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Titus doesn't reply -- probably a good sign.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Quit jumping to conclusions. Theo,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Quit jumping to conclusions. Theo," he turns to the old man, "you took that key. Did it look like it was *recently* put there?"

fields.Title: Alain: ""He lost his partner, the binoclard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He lost his partner, the binoclard. Cops can't function without their butt-buddies."

fields.Title: You: ""So you like waving your guns in pe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you like waving your guns in people's faces? Doesn't mean she does too."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Also inoperable?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Also inoperable?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Cop -- that's *exactly* what it me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cop -- that's *exactly* what it means."

fields.Title: You: ""You wouldn't believe the shit we h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You wouldn't believe the shit we have at the RCM."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""It's a *dumbwaiter*, not an indust..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a *dumbwaiter*, not an industrial lift. How about I go instead of..."

fields.Title: Half Light: "He's about to blow his fuse."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's about to blow his fuse.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I don't *know*." He smiles a pecul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't *know*." He smiles a peculiar smile. "I don't know where she went. She just up and left. Got real scared too. Wouldn't tell me where -- however *hard* I asked. Wanna know why?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You're a smart cop, but you're a s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're a smart cop, but you're a stupid person -- no one goes to tell Evrart anything. If he has to know, he has to know *fast*."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No. Her and Evrart -- they don't t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. Her and Evrart -- they don't talk. They've never met. They have no relations. They live in different *galaxies*. Get that through your head."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Scared? You should be too. A strang..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Scared? You should be too. A strange fear creeps over you, a metallic taste in your mouth. Change the subject.

fields.Title: Logic: "Really?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Really?

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""She said she's... building a..." H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She said she's... building a..." His voice is very quiet. "A pale emitter."

fields.Title: Logic: "No-no. He already said that, and no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No-no. He already said that, and nothing good came of it. Just do what the nice helpful guys said -- and *don't* do the bad things.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "And then when they're all empty, ju..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And then when they're all empty, just move on. Unto the next can. Don't look back -- unless there was something you *missed*.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Yeah, with us, drinking. Near the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, with us, drinking. Near the stage there." He points to the karaoke stage.

fields.Title: You: ""It's supra-natural -- a reality-br..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's supra-natural -- a reality-breaking event. And we just need to accept it."

fields.Title: Drama: "Sort of -- but *he* doesn't have to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sort of -- but *he* doesn't have to know that!

fields.Title: Logic: "This one's going into some kind of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This one's going into some kind of insane death spiral to preserve his version of the world.

fields.Title: Shanky: ""If she used us to cover her own sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If she used us to cover her own shit up... well, that's a serious violation of the *Hardie code*, boss."

fields.Title: You: ""Recent." (Nod.) "But they didn't f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Recent." (Nod.) "But they didn't fit with any of yours on the scene -- Ruby included."
fields.Alternate1: "Well, they didn't fit with any of yours on the scene -- Ruby included."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Right there, underneath the calm an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Right there, underneath the calm and the cool, a nervousness. He's thinking: Ruby could have fucked us all over. How did I not see it?

fields.Title: Logic: "That's a solid logic structure. Do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's a solid logic structure. Do something. This is bad.

fields.Title: Glen: "The blond man looks at the mushroom..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The blond man looks at the mushroomed deathbringer in the evidence bag and says:

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Tell you one thing: I liked how th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tell you one thing: I liked how that goddamn *winch* came up again. That was nifty."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Now what the *hell* are we suppose..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now what the *hell* are we supposed to do with that?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah, but the mambo jambo he's say..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, but the mambo jambo he's saying goes *against* his theory A."

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Boss..." The big guy in the corner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boss..." The big guy in the corner speaks up with a wheeze. "There's another in the kitchen. A blue door. I've been there..."

fields.Title: Shanky: ""He's been fuckin' *eating* in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's been fuckin' *eating* in the kitchen!" The rat-faced man explodes. "The cop and the lardo don't have shit."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You don't know. Just be honest."
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't know. Just be honest.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "You just showed him a breech-loadin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You just showed him a breech-loading gun!

fields.Title: Glen: ""Kitten?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kitten?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "And a little -- just a *little* --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And a little -- just a *little* -- worried.

fields.Title: You: ""Titus, you have to see it. Things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Titus, you have to see it. Things don't add up -- we need to talk to her." (Move on.)
fields.Alternate1: "Titus, you have to see it. Things don't add up. I need to talk to her." (Move on.)

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah, that's real *funny*. She was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, that's real *funny*. She wasn't laughing though." He looks at you.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""She's not far. We know that much -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She's not far. We know that much -- she didn't take her lorry. So she's on foot."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""When are you gonna get it through..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When are you gonna get it through your dumb head?" He scoffs. "I already *am*, I just wasn't sure you were."
fields.Alternate1: "When are you gonna get it through your suicidal head?" he scoffs. "I already *am* -- I just  wasn't sure you were."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "There's a *spooky* building West of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a *spooky* building West of this. Take a flashlight with you, search the basement. There are secrets -- magisterial, ancient secrets that may assist you.

fields.Title: Logic: "Sure. Why not? Let's hear what some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sure. Why not? Let's hear what some of our friends have to say.

fields.Title: Logic: "It's very unlikely to help, but sur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's very unlikely to help, but sure. We can go to Theory Town.

fields.Title: You: ""Ruby could have gone up -- shot hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby could have gone up -- shot him -- come down -- all under seven minutes."

fields.Title: Volition: "Blissful idiot -- say something. Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Blissful idiot -- say something. You've stood there for too long.

fields.Title: Authority: "Right. Puzzle Face shouldn't be the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Right. Puzzle Face shouldn't be the cool guy when he fails. *I* was supposed to be that.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Hey! Did someone say something alre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hey! Did someone say something already? No? Yes? Who cares! Upstairs, in Klaasje's bedroom -- the window the bullet came through. Analyse that!

fields.Title: You: ""*Or* she knew what happened, becau..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Or* she knew what happened, because she killed him."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Eugene wants a woman on the team so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Eugene wants a woman on the team so they can do their job. That must be *hard*. Half of Martinaise is female...

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He makes a gruff gesture for you to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He makes a gruff gesture for you to continue.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It wasn't that. I'm calling an end..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It wasn't that. I'm calling an end to this shit if you don't have anything better, cop."

fields.Title: You: ""Through what looks like an abandon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Through what looks like an abandoned pinball workshop."

fields.Title: You: ""That key I found here." (Point at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That key I found here." (Point at the window.) "Maybe it's for a secret route?"

fields.Title: You: ""In the *whole* 45-minute window --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In the *whole* 45-minute window -- she was with you *all the time*?"
fields.Alternate1: "You mean to say she stayed put from 11:30 to 12:15? *All* that time?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Well yeah... what do you expect? S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well yeah... what do you expect? She wasn't a f*g, of course she had babe-posters everywhere. You should see *my* fucking shack. Tits literally all over the place."

fields.Title: You: ""What do you mean *weird*, Theo?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean *weird*, Theo?"

fields.Title: You: ""She did tell us when we were close..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She did tell us when we were close to arresting her."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It's possible. Someone from their..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's possible. Someone from their own unit could have taken the shot -- from a spot on the coast, as I said. The roof's still the *sanest* choice for me."

fields.Title: You: ""Would you prefer to go on trial wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Would you prefer to go on trial with your friends -- as part of a lynch mob -- or alone, for committing murder?"

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Boss..." The big guy in the corner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boss..." The big guy in the corner speaks up with a wheeze. "There's another on the roof next to her window. Me and Tibbs saw it when we... were replacing..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Of course not." He scoffs. "And Ru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course not." He scoffs. "And Ruby didn't use your lost gun to kill him."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""There you go -- tatted on his ass...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There you go -- tatted on his ass. We know the place."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No you didn't. And Ruby didn't use..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No you didn't. And Ruby didn't use your lost gun to kill him."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Okay, I see your point -- there ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I see your point -- there are guns lying around." He shakes his head. "Dammit, I thought we'd found all the old spots. Why was that still there?"

fields.Title: You: ""That's right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Which is why we need to talk to he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Which is why we need to talk to her as soon as possible. There *is* grounds for a questioning here -- everyone sees that."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Angie -- check out what's behind t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Angie -- check out what's behind those doors when you get the time. It's probably nothing, but we need to know."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""The two are not mutually exclusive..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The two are not mutually exclusive. Get that through your fucking head." The man only slightly raises his voice.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That's right, Gene." He nods. "Now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, Gene." He nods. "Now, cop, you established a window of opportunity -- the only reason why you still have my ear. Don't waste it."

fields.Title: Authority: "He knows it's something. He's just..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He knows it's something. He's just not ready to say you knew more about Ruby than he does -- yet.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He must be referencing some past ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He must be referencing some past case of theirs.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "A very small nod -- and a trickle o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A very small nod -- and a trickle of tobacco spit on his lip.

fields.Title: You: ""She probably knew me from my singi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She probably knew me from my singing days."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""The coast is a dangerous place --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The coast is a dangerous place -- for *police*-men."

fields.Title: You: ""Is that true Kim? Am I a can-opene..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that true Kim? Am I a can-opener?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Evrart's file on you seemed thin on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Evrart's file on you seemed thin on info. She must know from somewhere else. From Jamrock. Something *more*.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Good fucking luck, man... She know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good fucking luck, man... She knows this place like the back of her hand. You'll never find her."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Can't get through the door? You kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Can't get through the door? You know what would help -- doing a *thorough* search of this room! Maybe something's hidden.

fields.Title: Logic: "Really?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Really?

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "The big guy smiles. "You got someth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The big guy smiles. "You got something else to back this route up? Or is that it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He sighs heavily. "Anything else yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sighs heavily. "Anything else you want, cop?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""There you have it. Pale-something...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There you have it. Pale-something." Titus puts an end to it.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "YES! Huff and puff and *blow* this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: YES! Huff and puff and *blow* this case wide open!

fields.Title: You: ""There is a secret route in the kit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There is a secret route in the kitchen that leads *straight* to the roof."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""So *that'*s what you were squintin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So *that'*s what you were squinting at." He looks at you. "You were trying to come up a theory, weren't you? That she did it."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Look who's finally speaking! Ratty'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look who's finally speaking! Ratty's been uncharacteristically quiet since you started theorizing. Maybe he has something to gain from implicating her?

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "He's been through it. That means *h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's been through it. That means *he's* suspected her too.

fields.Title: You: ""The people on the posters -- were..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The people on the posters -- were all women. One looked exactly like Klaasje."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Put the numbers out there. This *wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Put the numbers out there. This *will* impress them.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Fine. Don't impress them with balli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fine. Don't impress them with ballistics.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Why not? You can't draw a straight..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why not? You can't draw a straight line into Klaasje's window from any of the surrounding buildings -- not from what I know about Martinaise..."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Yeah, but that's what's so cool ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, but that's what's so cool about her!" The blond exclaims. "It's why we've been thinking..."

fields.Title: You: ""It's not 'why did she kill him?' -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not 'why did she kill him?' -- it's 'why did she organize the coverup?'."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Been thinking of getting *Whirling..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Been thinking of getting *Whirling-in-Rags* tatted on my ass, boss."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Of course."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""It's just two doors," he cuts in...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's just two doors," he cuts in. "We're not giving him *Ruby* for that -- she's one of *us*."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Nah, man -- she'd totally wave her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, man -- she'd totally wave her gun in *your* face if she were here right now. And you'd fucking PISS yourself."

fields.Title: You: ""It opens the kitchen door that lea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It opens the kitchen door that leads to the roof. You didn't find it, but Ruby did. That's how she got up there."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Goddamnit, we need to close that d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Goddamnit, we need to close that dump down for good."

fields.Title: You: ""It's an old building. There may be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an old building. There may be a secret passage -- or even a network of passages."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "I *told* you not to say that. This..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I *told* you not to say that. This is not a joking matter for him.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That's one mystery down then." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's one mystery down then." He nods. "An *architectural* mystery. It doesn't much concern Ruby, does it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yes -- you, the cop with the sideb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes -- you, the cop with the sideburns and the disco clothes."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You know, I don't usually do this -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know, I don't usually do this -- I just measure things, but...

fields.Title: Logic: "Let's move."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let's move.

fields.Title: Logic: "Absolutely nothing?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Absolutely nothing?

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know, but I'll find out.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know, but I'll find out."

fields.Title: Logic: "It's called a... radio, you believe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's called a... radio, you believe. The gardener may have played you again when she stormed out. She has her own plan.

fields.Title: Logic: "A sudden flash of lightning in your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A sudden flash of lightning in your neocortex -- the hostel-cafeteria is lit by its eerie blaze. Floor plans, bullet trajectories, webs of human emotion all channelled into a single thought...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "A massive activity spike in the *am..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A massive activity spike in the *amygdala copicum* -- the part cops use to pin murders on people.

fields.Title: Alain: ""He's cobbling together shit so he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's cobbling together shit so he can put her away. It's Cop 101."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Weird... how? You're wearing the pi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Weird... how? You're wearing the pinball maker's coat.

fields.Title: You: ""I analysed it on the spot. Turns o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I analysed it on the spot. Turns out I can do that."

fields.Title: Theo: ""Was run by a fella called..." He t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Was run by a fella called..." He thinks. "Nyflox something, who wore a yellow dust coat -- like the one you have on *right now*." He squints at you. "Weird guy. Never liked him."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You got his attention. Now don't ru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You got his attention. Now don't ruin it by making *weird* claims. Remember: you can still mess this up.

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's clear this one is protective o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's clear this one is protective of her.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "The big one. Get this and they'll g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The big one. Get this and they'll give her to you. Remember, don't piss him off. That never works.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Forty three is pretty large for a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Forty three is pretty large for a girl, don't you think?" He rubs his chin. "But then Ruby's what you call a *butch-girl* -- she's no daffodil."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Footprints." He takes a sip of his beer. "Recent?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Right -- what the fuck does that g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right -- what the fuck does that got to do with Ruby?"

fields.Title: Logic: "It doesn't fit *well*, but it fits...."
fields.Dialogue Text: It doesn't fit *well*, but it fits. And he knows it.

fields.Title: Glen: ""That'd be awesome, I've beat that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That'd be awesome, I've beat that Royalist machine twenty times now."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Alright alright, we can get the ba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright alright, we can get the barman to bring them down -- what else?"

fields.Title: You: ""She could have made a copy.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "She could have made a copy."

fields.Title: You: ""There's a cellar under the booksho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a cellar under the bookshop. It was hidden there -- with others just like it."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Not maybe. You *were*." He points..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not maybe. You *were*." He points at the lieutenant. "Both of you. I've done it myself, gone and piled every thread I find onto one theory. Doesn't work like that."

fields.Title: You: ""I have analysed the bullet that ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have analysed the bullet that killed him -- it was jacketed."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""What are you gonna cry now?" He sq..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you gonna cry now?" He squints at you, as if inspecting how close to crying you are.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Organized crime -- down in Jamrock..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Organized crime -- down in Jamrock probably. He's not being *too* forthcoming -- this is not a surprise.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "No, just say you're honest with him..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, just say you're honest with him, don't *challenge* him.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I don't have to *believe*. I know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't have to *believe*. I know you ain't got shit." He squints at you.

fields.Title: You: ""I've already established Ruby's ru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've already established Ruby's running drugs. She could've smuggled guns too."

fields.Title: You: ""So she didn't go to tell Evrart.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So she didn't go to tell Evrart."

fields.Title: You: ""What was she scared of?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What was she scared of?"

fields.Title: You: ""When did she leave?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "When did she leave?"

fields.Title: You: ""It's not much, but it'll do." (Go!..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not much, but it'll do." (Go!)

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Not just granite -- tightly packed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not just granite -- tightly packed RCM sergeant material.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It seems you have that effect -- e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It seems you have that effect -- especially on *women*." He looks at you.

fields.Title: Logic: "*Evrart* has a file on you, but tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Evrart* has a file on you, but that's bogus. What she knows comes from somewhere else -- from Jamrock. It must be *real* stuff.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You are... insistent." He nods."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You are... insistent." He nods.

fields.Title: Logic: "Easy! If the lieutenant isn't here,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Easy! If the lieutenant isn't here, you should find him and attempt this again while he's with you.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Hey! Did someone say something alre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hey! Did someone say something already? No? Yes? Who cares! Upstairs, in Klaasje's bedroom -- the window the bullet came through. Analyse that!

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Reporting for duty! A *thorough* se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reporting for duty! A *thorough* search of this Union box may help unearth something *incriminating*! Pin it on her -- she's been here, right?

fields.Title: Volition: "You could crack that Klaasje's defe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could crack that Klaasje's defences. Maybe she'll tell you something helpful?

fields.Title: Logic: "Gladly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Gladly.

fields.Title: Logic: "... No one?"
fields.Dialogue Text: ... No one?

fields.Title: Logic: "Just me, huh? Wow. Well... Good luc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just me, huh? Wow. Well... Good luck!

fields.Title: Alain: ""That's sad, man -- but why are you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's sad, man -- but why are you squinting like that?" The tattooed man leans closer. "Looks to me like he's about to get aggressive."

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You should say: I need to kill myse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should say: I need to kill myself and it's all over!

fields.Title: You: ""She's right. I won't.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "She's right. I won't."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Titus's gaze meets yours: "Yeah, so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Titus's gaze meets yours: "Yeah, so...?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ruby could have gone up -- shot hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby could have gone up -- shot him -- come down -- all under seven minutes."

fields.Title: Glen: ""But she didn't! She would *never*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But she didn't! She would *never* do that." The blond man looks around. "Why aren't more of you defending her? This is fucking stupid, Titus."

fields.Title: You: ""I didn't say I'd *prove* she had t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't say I'd *prove* she had the murder weapon -- just that we need to find her." (Move on.)

fields.Title: Alain: ""No -- but that doesn't prove anyth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No -- but that doesn't prove anything."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And even then -- a route doesn't p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And even then -- a route doesn't put that bullet in the merc's head. A gun does that. And Ruby doesn't carry one."

fields.Title: Logic: "Is it? It *proves* there are things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is it? It *proves* there are things about the Whirling-in-Rags that he doesn't know. He *must* see that.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This was merely a thought exercise..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This was merely a thought exercise. He did not lose his gun. Let's move on."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""There's *another*, right on the ro..."]
Authority: "Wait, did he say you don't have *bi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, did he say you don't have *big guns*?

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Why?" He shakes his head. "This do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why?" He shakes his head. "This doesn't make sense. It's damn *interesting*, but it doesn't fit well and you know it."

fields.Title: You: ""Just because it's rare doesn't mea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just because it's rare doesn't mean you can't get it."

fields.Title: You: ""Fine, Titus -- I'm not getting int..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine, Titus -- I'm not getting into it, if it touches on your precious business."

fields.Title: Logic: "He's angry because he knows you're..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's angry because he knows you're right. What he's saying only confirms your theory.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Fucking hell..." The tattooed man..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fucking hell..." The tattooed man shakes his head. "Titus, did he just..."

fields.Title: You: ""Don't forget the *funny* tie too.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't forget the *funny* tie too."

fields.Title: You: ""You said it would be nice to have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You said it would be nice to have a ballistics lab. Use ours -- turn this into a real police force."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "And he still isn't. People aren't a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And he still isn't. People aren't afraid of good cops in the way Ruby was afraid of you, he thinks, then turns back to his men.

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper) "Kim, you've had long eno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper) "Kim, you've had long enough to come up with a theory. What'cha got?"

fields.Title: You: ""The elevator is on the *outer wall..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The elevator is on the *outer wall* of the building. It's an old dumbwaiter -- used for moving pinball machines up and down from the workshop."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "The big guy takes a long, considere..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The big guy takes a long, considered gulp of beer. "And? How does she come into it?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'll start there. One more questio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'll start there. One more question: what does Ruby look like?"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Say something. If you say something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say something. If you say something you can jolt out of the stupor. Just one sentence. Here we go...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ehm..." The lieutenant puts his ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ehm..." The lieutenant puts his hand on your shoulder. "Unless we have more business, we should..." He looks to the door.

fields.Title: You: ""Five hundred Lears and I can't rem..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Five hundred Lears and I can't remember the first line."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You know, I'm beginning to think t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know, I'm beginning to think this clown is squinting at me..." He looks around. "...because he wants to start something."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "He fires a nod of solidarity in you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He fires a nod of solidarity in your direction, as if to say: take your time. It's okay.

fields.Title: Volition: "You could crack Klaasje's last defe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could crack Klaasje's last defences. Maybe she'll tell you something helpful?

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Hey! Lost gun right here! Lost and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hey! Lost gun right here! Lost and found!

fields.Title: Half Light: "It's the kind of chin-rubbing men -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's the kind of chin-rubbing men -- often leaders -- do when they think of *punishment*.

fields.Title: You: ""Why are you so sure Ruby *didn't*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you so sure Ruby *didn't* off him?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He thinks for a moment, then nods a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He thinks for a moment, then nods and says : "Good news is -- I'm still listening."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ruby then threatened her -- and to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby then threatened her -- and told her to end her relationship with the deceased."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Figures." He looks out the window...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Figures." He looks out the window. "But that Ruby *is* queer as cabaret, now that I start thinking about it. So there is some truth to it..."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Those numbers were an *ass-pull*,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Those numbers were an *ass-pull*, man."

fields.Title: Composure: "It *is* a very comfortable coat for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It *is* a very comfortable coat for such an oldie...

fields.Title: Alain: ""See boss, they're contradicting th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "See boss, they're contradicting themselves. Now they're saying it *wasn't* the roof. They can't put her there, it's all bullshit."

fields.Title: You: ""Klaasje told me some pretty *inter..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Klaasje told me some pretty *interesting* things about Ruby."
fields.Alternate1: "Before I arrested Klaasje she told me some pretty *interesting* things about Ruby."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And I suppose you have a theory ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And I suppose you have a theory about that too, cop?"

fields.Title: Shanky: ""I didn't do it, fucker! It wasn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't do it, fucker! It wasn't *my* plan."
