fields.Title: Eugene: "He scoffs."
fields.Dialogue Text: He scoffs.

fields.Title: Drama: "The tracks were recent -- but *not*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tracks were recent -- but *not* worn down in the right foot like Ruby's. It's best to *omit* this pesky little polemic for now. Too *confusing*.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What if those two doors are connec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if those two doors are connected, Eugene? Is that your name -- Eugene?" The lieutenant leans closer.
fields.Alternate1: The lieutenant leans closer to Eugene. "What if they're connected by the *winch*, Eugene? That is your, name, right -- Eugene?"

fields.Title: You: "(Hold out the bullet) "This is the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Hold out the bullet) "This is the bullet that did it -- 4.46 mm. The Belle-Magrave uses the same calibre."

fields.Title: Logic: "He sees it -- this is coming togeth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sees it -- this is coming together -- he *must*.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Time to really close the deal. Show..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time to really close the deal. Show them the bullet.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yes, god damn it, I know what a 72..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, god damn it, I know what a 72% chance means. It means there's a 28% chance it *isn't* that." He thinks for a moment. "And 28% is no small chance either."

fields.Title: Alain: ""It does?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It does?"

fields.Title: You: "(Show them the antique rifle.) "The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Show them the antique rifle.) "There are weapons like this just lying around in Martinaise."

fields.Title: Logic: "Still. The key here is a strange co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still. The key here is a strange coincidence -- and he knows it.

fields.Title: You: ""That still leaves a 72% chance it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That still leaves a 72% chance it *did*."

fields.Title: You: ""C'mon guys, she's one of you. Of c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon guys, she's one of you. Of course she's carrying -- you all are."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Shush now." He turns to you. "You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shush now." He turns to you. "You got something else to back this route up? Or is that it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Nah..." He taps his coat pocket. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah..." He taps his coat pocket. "This kind of heat is not easy to come by. It took us some time get *gunned up* to where we are now."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You were warned not to bring it up...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You were warned not to bring it up. Your best shot here is to just back out of it.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure -- *normal*," he says without..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure -- *normal*," he says without smiling.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah -- I see it." He puts his bee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- I see it." He puts his beer down. "There's one more thing I've been *wondering* about. Ever since you asked me where she is. Add it to your list of suspicions, if you want."

fields.Title: You: "Walk away."
fields.Dialogue Text: Walk away.

fields.Title: You: ""Won't stop?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Won't stop?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""How can I forget." He nods at your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How can I forget." He nods at your tie.
fields.Alternate1: "How can I forget." He nods at your tie.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""More precisely? On the *coast*. Pa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "More precisely? On the *coast*. Past the water lock." He nods southwest. "She's not here, so I'm thinking she's there."

fields.Title: Logic: "It's that simple."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's that simple.

fields.Title: You: "Got it. Now get me moving again, pl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Got it. Now get me moving again, please.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Still, there's definitely somethin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Still, there's definitely something there to check out..." He turns the Eugene. "We need to have a look at that secret passage, boys."

fields.Title: Logic: "Sorry. You're not coming up with an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sorry. You're not coming up with anything. Again, the pieces are there: she could have done it, somehow, something else, wala-wala-bing-bang -- it's just not coming together.

fields.Title: You: "(Squint your eyes harder.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: (Squint your eyes harder.)

fields.Title: Endurance: "Go out and run circles around the b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Go out and run circles around the building until you come up with something. Whatever you do, don't stand here anymore.

fields.Title: Logic: "No-no! Nothing good will come of it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No-no! Nothing good will come of it -- he did the right thing not saying that the last time. Just do what the nice helpful guys said -- and *don't* do the bad things.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Reporting for duty! A *thorough* se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reporting for duty! A *thorough* search of this Union box may help unearth something *incriminating*! Pin it on her -- she's been here, right?

fields.Title: You: "Let's not get dramatic."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let's not get dramatic.

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe she killed him because she t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe she killed him because she thought it would curry favour with you?"

fields.Title: You: ""Recent." (Nod.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Recent." (Nod.)

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe it's all part of a leadershi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe it's all part of a leadership challenge? Against you, Titus."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""She didn't tell you shit." He shak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She didn't tell you shit." He shakes his head. "If she did, it was lies."

fields.Title: Logic: "This complex operation is probably..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This complex operation is probably something illegal.

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Yeah but..." The fat man looks up..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah but..." The fat man looks up from the table, oblivious. "They're both girls."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Good one.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good one."

fields.Title: You: ""Apparently she had a *thing* for K..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apparently she had a *thing* for Klaasje."

fields.Title: You: ""Guys, this is Revachol. Anyone cou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Guys, this is Revachol. Anyone could get a gun around here. *Anyone*."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes. Big lab. Back in Jamrock. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Big lab. Back in Jamrock. The... Jamrock Ballistics Lab."
fields.Alternate1: "Yes. We have a ballistics lab in Couron we consult in cases like these."

fields.Title: You: ""You *do* agree the shot came from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You *do* agree the shot came from the roof, right?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That's quite the theory..." He tur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's quite the theory..." He turns to Eugene. "We need to have a look at that secret passage, boys."

fields.Title: Logic: "Phase III: Motive. The last compone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Phase III: Motive. The last component.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The lieutenant is glad he got the f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant is glad he got the floor plan right there.

fields.Title: You: ""There's a door downstairs in the k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a door downstairs in the kitchen -- a locked *blue* door. Ever been through that?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Right." Titus nods. "And that's mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." Titus nods. "And that's mighty forthcoming of you, so let me extend you the same courtesy: she's connected. To you-know-what."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Garbage." He crosses his arms. "It..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Garbage." He crosses his arms. "It wasn't a Sam Bo artist, cop. I've been doing this for ten years -- let me give you a lesson. Boys?"

fields.Title: You: ""A skilled *Sam Bo artist* could ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A skilled *Sam Bo artist* could have climbed the outer wall, like a spider..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Silence. He looks around the room."
fields.Dialogue Text: Silence. He looks around the room.

fields.Title: You: ""You think she knew I'd find eviden..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You think she knew I'd find evidence against her?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "And a hole in his heart. That first..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And a hole in his heart. That first.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No one goes to tell Evrart anythin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No one goes to tell Evrart anything. He knows what he has to know -- fast."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "His grip is firm and reassuring. Li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His grip is firm and reassuring. Like holding a piece of unpolished granite.

fields.Title: You: "Just think it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just think it.

fields.Title: You: "No, I want to do this all by myself..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, I want to do this all by myself!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks around the roo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks around the room, evidently enjoying the moment's respite. But before long, he puts his hand on your shoulder. "Unless we have more business, we should..." He looks to the door.

fields.Title: Logic: "Absolutely nothing?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Absolutely nothing?

fields.Title: Glen: ""But she didn't! This is fucking st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But she didn't! This is fucking stupid, Titus. This and the queer thing, all of it!" The blond man looks around. "Why aren't more of you defending her? This is fucking stupid, Titus."

fields.Title: Logic: "Of course! Ruby is the lady driver..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course! Ruby is the lady driver in this great big *Jam Mystery*! Probably. You'll have to keep investigating -- they'll never open up about it.

fields.Title: You: ""My wife left me and I'm completely..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My wife left me and I'm completely alone."

fields.Title: Volition: "Your mouth is open. Close it. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your mouth is open. Close it. It's really, really going to help if you do.

fields.Title: Logic: "No one knows."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one knows.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Please, please do not melt down aga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Please, please do not melt down again. We're so close to wrapping this up and getting out of here.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "There's a *spooky* building West of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a *spooky* building West of this. Take a flashlight with you, search the basement. There are secrets -- magisterial, ancient secrets that may assist you.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You had expressed -- on occasion -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You had expressed -- on occasion -- your dislike of the mercenaries' presence in Martinaise, right?"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Betrayal is not painless. Even a do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Betrayal is not painless. Even a doubt of it hurts.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""She was here all night?" The lieut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She was here all night?" The lieutenant ignores the tattooed man. "11:30 to 12:15 -- she was here during *all* that time?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A more logical conclusion -- that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A more logical conclusion -- that you wish to avoid -- is that she knew what had happened, because she *did it*."

fields.Title: You: ""Klaasje said Ruby *takes care* of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Klaasje said Ruby *takes care* of things. You don't do that without a gun in Revachol."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Yeah, he was cobbling together shi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, he was cobbling together shit. So he could put her away -- it's RCM 101."

fields.Title: Logic: "The window Klaasje gave for the tim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The window Klaasje gave for the time of death was From 11:30 to 12:15.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Man, now he's just throwing shit a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Man, now he's just throwing shit against the wall to see what sticks."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Liberal, man? Ruby's like a hard c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liberal, man? Ruby's like a hard core patriot. You'd have to be blind not to..." He looks around. "Guys, I'm not the only one who *knew*, right?"

fields.Title: You: ""It's scary, yes. She probably went..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's scary, yes. She probably went to a University and learned it from a *liberal*."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""She's not a ghost, she's gay. You'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She's not a ghost, she's gay. You'd have to be an idiot not to..." He looks around. "Guys, I'm not the only one who knew, right?"

fields.Title: Glen: ""Look, fucko --" Glen steps forward..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, fucko --" Glen steps forward. "Ruby and I are pretty tight. She would have showed me the gun if she had one. She knows I love guns."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""A thing? You mean..." He tilts his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A thing? You mean..." He tilts his head to the side and falls silent.

fields.Title: Logic: "He knows they *had* to be recent fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He knows they *had* to be recent for those lines to still read. This wasn't a failure.

fields.Title: You: ""A little thing -- Ruby had these p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A little thing -- Ruby had these posters in her truck. Old movie stars."

fields.Title: Glen: ""T, we're not seriously considering..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "T, we're not seriously considering it, are we?!" He almost gets up from his seat. "Ruby wouldn't do this. Why would she do something like this?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He thinks for a moment, then nods a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He thinks for a moment, then nods and says : "Good news is -- I'm still listening."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""*Horizontal*? I see they taught yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Horizontal*? I see they taught you well in your RCM school. My old man -- a hunter and a half blind one at that -- could've said that. Horizontal lines..."

fields.Title: You: ""There's a locked door on the roof...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a locked door on the roof. Leading *to* the roof. Ever seen that?"

fields.Title: You: ""*Workshop Spare* actually. It was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Workshop Spare* actually. It was in *your* box. Ruby's been here, right?"

fields.Title: Fat Angus: ""Whoaa....""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whoaa...."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yes." He pinches the root of his n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." He pinches the root of his nose.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""So...?" The man shrugs and looks a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So...?" The man shrugs and looks at you.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. I'm never solving th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. I'm never solving this case, it's too *complicated*."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Screw honest -- you just *showed* h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Screw honest -- you just *showed* him a breech-loading gun!

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""But a route," he forms a gun with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But a route," he forms a gun with his hand, "does not put that bullet in his head. A gun does that. And Ruby doesn't carry one."

fields.Title: Logic: "That's all you needed. Doubt."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's all you needed. Doubt.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""...open Angus up like a can? Yes,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...open Angus up like a can? Yes, he did." He nods. "Now, we can whine about it, whack him, or we can go on with our lives. I'm having a 'go on with our lives' kind of day, Al. How about you?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Like the RCM?" He lets go of your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like the RCM?" He lets go of your hand. "You're a real police force all right -- of the Wild Pines. Everyone around here knows that. So watch your ass out there."

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's not a threat -- it's a warning..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not a threat -- it's a warning.

fields.Title: You: ""Anything else? *Anything*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anything else? *Anything*?"

fields.Title: Horrific Necktie: "You and I are going to dance in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You and I are going to dance in the moonlight under a billion stars.

fields.Title: You: ""Through a secret passage.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Through a secret passage."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""You got it boss! Professional law..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You got it boss! Professional law enforcement will investigate."

fields.Title: Glen: ""Which is why she didn't! This is f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Which is why she didn't! This is fucking stupid, Titus. This and the queer thing, all of it!" The blond man waves his beer around. "Why aren't more of you defending her? This is fucking stupid, Titus."

fields.Title: Logic: "This guy barely understands what he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This guy barely understands what he's talking about.

fields.Title: Drama: "No, no! He needs to say: "Five hund..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, no! He needs to say: "Five hundred Lears and I can't remember the first line!"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "His wife left him. He needs to kill..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His wife left him. He needs to kill himself -- make her sorry she did.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Also, you should say: I need to kil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Also, you should say: I need to kill myself and it's all over!

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Nah boss, he's just mentally handi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah boss, he's just mentally handicapped. I've seen them do that."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Because she was here *all night*...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because she was here *all night*. With us."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""How...?" He looks sincerely curiou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How...?" He looks sincerely curious.

fields.Title: You: ""She didn't go out for fresh air --..."

fields.Dialogue Text: "A broken old broomstick is what you showed me -- but point taken." He nods.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "No -- he already is a sergeant. Tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No -- he already is a sergeant. That's what you're feeling. He just wasn't sure what *you* are.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""The coast is a dangerous place.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The coast is a dangerous place."
fields.Alternate1: "The coast is a dangerous place for lawmen. Especially Mr. Can Opener here."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "The big man pinches the bridge of h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The big man pinches the bridge of his nose. "Course you do, clown. Of fucking course. That's how you do it in the Revachol Circus Militia."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Cop, I'm gonna stop you right ther..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cop, I'm gonna stop you right there." He pushes up his hat. "I'll save you the embarrassment -- I won't force you to tell me you've not been back there."

fields.Title: Logic: "Oh no, he's stuck again. Please, so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh no, he's stuck again. Please, someone -- just animate him. I got nothing.

fields.Title: You: "No, no -- we can do this. (Squint y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, no -- we can do this. (Squint your eyes.)

fields.Title: Logic: "I don't know what it means, but it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know what it means, but it felt like the most appropriate thing to say. That's what the *Witch Doctor* would say, at least.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No, no." The lieutenant looks at y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, no." The lieutenant looks at you with slight worry. "That's his... concentration face."

fields.Title: Logic: "Say... Hard to remember with your b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say... Hard to remember with your brain in overload, but have you smoked lately? A cigarette may help you.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Plus, man, it's like *female intui..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Plus, man, it's like *female intuition* you know. Women talk to women." He peeks at Titus. "Which is sorta why we need someone on the team who they talk to."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Yeah..." The man seems unsure of h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah..." The man seems unsure of himself.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""What else could you make out -- *h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else could you make out -- *how* recent? What size?"

fields.Title: You: ""She didn't go to the bar -- for a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She didn't go to the bar -- for a drink?"

fields.Title: You: ""What Kim said.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What Kim said."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That Ruby is queer as cabaret, now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That Ruby is queer as cabaret, now that I start thinking about it. I don't know I why didn't see it earlier..." He looks out the window, pensively.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Don't take me wrong, I love to sta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't take me wrong, I love to stare at broads on posters, but we're talking about a *murder* here."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He thinks for a moment, then nods:..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He thinks for a moment, then nods: "Good news is -- I'm still listening."

fields.Title: You: ""C'mon, guys. She hangs out with yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, guys. She hangs out with you meatheads. This cannot come as a surprise."

fields.Title: Alain: ""See boss, he's contradicting himse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "See boss, he's contradicting himself. Now he's saying it *wasn't* the roof. They can't put her there, it's all bullshit."

fields.Title: Shanky: "The little man squints, eyes beady...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The little man squints, eyes beady. "She had, like, a fully formed plan and shit. Right when she came back downstairs..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Glen." Titus looks grim. "I though..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Glen." Titus looks grim. "I thought the same thing when she skipped town and left us in this shit."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "The big man leans closer. "Tell me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The big man leans closer. "Tell me -- did you lose it *before* the murder?"

fields.Title: Logic: "This man is smarter than he looks...."
fields.Dialogue Text: This man is smarter than he looks. We can work with this.

fields.Title: You: ""There is a small -- 28% -- chance..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There is a small -- 28% -- chance that shot came from *beyond* the roof."

fields.Title: You: ""What if they're somehow connected..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if they're somehow connected to the murder -- a *Pinball Murderer*?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Goddamn, that's just about your fa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Goddamn, that's just about your favourite topic isn't it?" Titus slaps his thigh. "Every fucking five seconds!"

fields.Title: You: ""And the hole in his heart.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And the hole in his heart."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Perhaps." He looks out of the wind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Perhaps." He looks out of the window again. "Ask her if you find her. It won't be easy though. She made sure of that."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We will start there." The lieutena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We will start there." The lieutenant takes a quick note. "One more question: what does Ruby look like?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure -- there are some shithouses..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure -- there are some shithouses there. A cinderblock town. The fisher-folk there refuse to unionise, so that's one place we haven't looked."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Friday afternoon. When you first a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Friday afternoon. When you first arrived. I got word the RCM was in town, then she came in to see me. Told me she was leaving. That's when we had our little... conversation."

fields.Title: You: ""What else did Ruby tell you -- abo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else did Ruby tell you -- about me?"

fields.Title: You: ""Where have you looked for her?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where have you looked for her?"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "For starters, you could search the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For starters, you could search the Whirling-in-Rags for hidden passages she could have used to get to the roof. There's a door in the *kitchen* I've had my eye on for a while...

fields.Title: You: "Not just yet -- can't we review the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not just yet -- can't we review the components of the theory?
